{
  "texts": [
    "There exist three strategies for mapping a computational kernel onto systolic arrays: namely Output Stationary (OS), Input Stationary (IS), and Weight Stationary (WS) [32].",
    "The \"stationary\" term determines which vector among the input, weight, or output remains fixed within the PE during the computation.",
    "Fig. 3 shows the OS data flow in the systolic array as an example.",
    "The selection of a configuration plays an important role as it influences the total number of compute cycles.",
    "The WS/IS dataflow involves preloading the stationary matrix onto the PEs prior to the computational tasks, making them suitable for scenarios where one of the matrices is reused repeatedly."
  ]
}